familyName.title: familyName
familyName.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of an Person. This can be used along with givenName instead of the name property.

gtin.title: gtin
gtin.description: A Global Trade Item Number (GTIN). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes. The gtin property generalizes the earlier gtin8, gtin12, gtin13, and gtin14 properties. The GS1 digital link specifications express GTINs as URLs. A correct gtin value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a valid GS1 check digit and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also GS1's GTIN Summary and Wikipedia for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged.

sameAs.title: sameAs
sameAs.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

partOfSeries.title: partOfSeries
partOfSeries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

composer.title: composer
composer.description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

possibleTreatment.title: possibleTreatment
possibleTreatment.description: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

creator.title: creator
creator.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

elevation.title: elevation
elevation.description: The elevation of a location (WGS 84). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNITOFMEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

hasOccupation.title: hasOccupation
hasOccupation.description: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

founder.title: founder
founder.description: A person who founded this organization.

unitCode.title: unitCode
unitCode.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

director.title: director
director.description: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

duns.title: duns
duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

foundingLocation.title: foundingLocation
foundingLocation.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

legalStatus.title: legalStatus
legalStatus.description: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

latitude.title: latitude
latitude.description: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

producer.title: producer
producer.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

geo.title: geo
geo.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

about.title: about
about.description: The subject matter of the content.

subEvent.title: subEvent
subEvent.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

memberOf.title: memberOf
memberOf.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

numberOfSeasons.title: numberOfSeasons
numberOfSeasons.description: The number of seasons in this series.

locationCreated.title: locationCreated
locationCreated.description: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

exampleOfWork.title: exampleOfWork
exampleOfWork.description: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

image.title: image
image.description: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

hasPart.title: hasPart
hasPart.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

license.title: license
license.description: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

position.title: position
position.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

material.title: material
material.description: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

genre.title: genre
genre.description: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

issueNumber.title: issueNumber
issueNumber.description: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

issn.title: issn
issn.description: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

affiliation.title: affiliation
affiliation.description: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

minValue.title: minValue
minValue.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

colorist.title: colorist
colorist.description: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

partOfSeason.title: partOfSeason
partOfSeason.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

broadcastChannelId.title: broadcastChannelId
broadcastChannelId.description: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

owns.title: owns
owns.description: Products owned by the organization or person.

leiCode.title: leiCode
leiCode.description: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

competitor.title: competitor
competitor.description: A competitor in a sports event.

maxValue.title: maxValue
maxValue.description: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

lyricist.title: lyricist
lyricist.description: The person who wrote the words.

relevantSpecialty.title: relevantSpecialty
relevantSpecialty.description: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

brand.title: brand
brand.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

superEvent.title: superEvent
superEvent.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

volumeNumber.title: volumeNumber
volumeNumber.description: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

provider.title: provider
provider.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

callSign.title: callSign
callSign.description: A callsign, as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

numberOfPages.title: numberOfPages
numberOfPages.description: The number of pages in the book.

containedInPlace.title: containedInPlace
containedInPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

parentOrganization.title: parentOrganization
parentOrganization.description: The larger organization that this organization is a subOrganization of, if any.

foundingDate.title: foundingDate
foundingDate.description: The date that this organization was founded.

containsPlace.title: containsPlace
containsPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

contentLocation.title: contentLocation
contentLocation.description: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

encodingFormat.title: encodingFormat
encodingFormat.description:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).

In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

contributor.title: contributor
contributor.description: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

iswcCode.title: iswcCode
iswcCode.description: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

duration.title: duration
duration.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.

startDate.title: startDate
startDate.description: The start date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

translator.title: translator
translator.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

copyrightHolder.title: copyrightHolder
copyrightHolder.description: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

dissolutionDate.title: dissolutionDate
dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

countryOfOrigin.title: countryOfOrigin
countryOfOrigin.description: The country of the principal offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie or program.

worksFor.title: worksFor
worksFor.description: Organizations that the person works for.

inLanguage.title: inLanguage
inLanguage.description: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

publisher.title: publisher
publisher.description: The publisher of the creative work.

numberOfEmployees.title: numberOfEmployees
numberOfEmployees.description: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

value.title: value
value.description:
The value of the quantitative value or property value node.

  • For QuantitativeValue and MonetaryAmount, the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
  • For PropertyValue, it can be 'Text;', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

isBasedOn.title: isBasedOn
isBasedOn.description: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaption.

releaseOf.title: releaseOf
releaseOf.description: The album this is a release of.

gender.title: gender
gender.description: Gender of something, typically a Person, but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While http://schema.org/Male and http://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender. The gender property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender SportsTeam can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

deathPlace.title: deathPlace
deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

musicReleaseFormat.title: musicReleaseFormat
musicReleaseFormat.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

knowsLanguage.title: knowsLanguage
knowsLanguage.description: Of a Person, and less typically of an Organization, to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

iataCode.title: iataCode
iataCode.description: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

actor.title: actor
actor.description: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

byArtist.title: byArtist
byArtist.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

author.title: author
author.description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

connectedTo.title: connectedTo
connectedTo.description: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

location.title: location
location.description: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

subOrganization.title: subOrganization
subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

award.title: award
award.description: An award won by or for this item.

workExample.title: workExample
workExample.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

contentRating.title: contentRating
contentRating.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

weight.title: weight
weight.description: The weight of the product or person.

birthPlace.title: birthPlace
birthPlace.description: The place where the person was born.

homeLocation.title: homeLocation
homeLocation.description: A contact location for a person's residence.

honorificPrefix.title: honorificPrefix
honorificPrefix.description: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

netWorth.title: netWorth
netWorth.description: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

signOrSymptom.title: signOrSymptom
signOrSymptom.description: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

citation.title: citation
citation.description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

productionCompany.title: productionCompany
productionCompany.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

endDate.title: endDate
endDate.description: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

riskFactor.title: riskFactor
riskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

pagination.title: pagination
pagination.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

editor.title: editor
editor.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

givenName.title: givenName
givenName.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person. This can be used along with familyName instead of the name property.

numberOfEpisodes.title: numberOfEpisodes
numberOfEpisodes.description: The number of episodes in this season or series.

alumniOf.title: alumniOf
alumniOf.description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

isPartOf.title: isPartOf
isPartOf.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

dateCreated.title: dateCreated
dateCreated.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

sponsor.title: sponsor
sponsor.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

recordLabel.title: recordLabel
recordLabel.description: The label that issued the release.

longitude.title: longitude
longitude.description: The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

character.title: character
character.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.
